|| Video 12 ORM and JPA and Spring Data Jpa||

*ORM
->  ORM = Object Relational Maping
-> ORM is a technique used to map java objects to database tables.
-> it allows developers to work with database using object-oriented programing concepts , making it easier to
interact with relational database.
-> for example :- hamare pass class hai user name ki and database me ek table hai users name agar ham user wale
class pe operation perform karte hai to orm ki madat se users table me bhi whai operation hojayega.
-> Consider a java class User and a database table users.
-> ORM framework like Hibernet can map the fields in the User class to columns in the user table,
makin it easier to insert, update, retrieve, and delete records.
-> ORM ki madat se user class ke andar jobhi fields hai wo user table me columns ke andar map hojayengi hame easy kardega
insert, update, delete, and retrieve karne ko.

*JPA
-> JPA = Java Persistence API
-> Persistence = permanently store karna data ko
-> API = set of rules
-> JPA set of rules provide karta hai jisse ham ORM achive kar shakte hai.
-> JPA is a way to achive ORM, includes interfaces and annotations that you use in your Java calsses, requires a
presistence provider (ORM tools) for implementation.
-> JPA ek set of rules hai iske annotaion and interface hoti hai apni java class ki ye khud se kuch nhai karegi
hamko ORM ke tools chaiye honge inko implement karne ke liye.
*presistence provider (ORM tools)
-> To use JPA, you need a presistence provider. A presistence provider is a specific implementaion of the JPA
specification. Examples of JPA persistence providers include Hibernate, EclipseLink, and OpenJPA. These providers
implement the JPA interfaces and provide the underlying functionality to interact with database.
-> JPA interface ki kai sari implementaion ho shakti hai jaise ki Hibernate, EclipseLink, and OpenJPA(ORM Tools) ham JPA in teen
tareeko se use karenge piche wale tareeko se. actual me ham Hibernate, EclipseLink, and OpenJPA ye teen chiz use kar
rhae honge to interact with relational database

*Spring Data JPA
-> Spring Data JPA is built on top of the JPA(java presistenace api) specification, but it is not a JPA implementation
itself. instead, it simplifies working with JPA by providing higher-level abstractions and utilites. however, to use
Spring Data JPA effectively, you still need a JPA implementation, such as Hibernate, EclipseLink, or another JPA-compliant
provider, to handle the actual database interactions.
-> Spring Data JPA ki madat se ham log chizo or chippa shakte hai abstractions ki madat se.

----> JPA is primarily designed for working with relational database, where data is stored in tables with a predefined
schema. Mongo DB, on the other hand, is a NoSql database that uses a different data model, typically based on collections
of documents, which are schema-less or have flexible schemas. this fundamental differnce in data models and storage
structures is why JPA IS NOT USED IN MONFODB.
-> 🔥 Final ek line me:

   👉 SQL = "pehle schema banao, fir data daalo" // strict rules it is a relational database
   👉 MongoDB = "pehle data daalo, schema baad me bhi chalega" // freedom or flexible

-> In the case of Mongodb, you dont have tadtional JPA persistence provider. MOngo db is a NOSQL database , and SPRING
DATA MONGODB  serves as the "persistence provider" for MONGODB,
-> It Proivedes the necessary abstraction and implementaion to work with MONGODB in a Spring application.

-> ham log database ke shaat khel shakte hai do chizo ki madat se QUERY METHOD DSL and  CRITERIA API in dono
ki madat se ham database ke shat interact kar shakte hai when using Spring Data JPA for relational database and
Spring Data Mongodb for mongodb data base.

-> Spring Data JPA is a part of the Spring framework that simplifies data access in java applications, while Spring
Data Mongodb provides similar functionality for Mongodb.

-> QUERY METHOD DSL isme hame querry lhikni ki jarrurat nhai hai method ka name lhikna hai iss tarah se ki wo
querry ban jaye bhot easy hai matlab bhot easy
-> CRITERIA API ye use hota hai complex and custom queries bana ne ke liye ye bhi bhot easy hai matlab bhot easy.
-> QUERY METHOD DSL and  CRITERIA API ye do chiz aane ke baad database hamare finger tips pe hoga matlab easyli ham
interact kar payenge database ke shaat.

